<div class="profile-pic">
<img alt="Julia Chisholm, Consultant Paediatric Oncologist" border="0" id="ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_PlaceHolderMain_column1Content_column1Content_OtherStaffList_TeamMemberRepeater_ctl01_ctl00_MemberPhoto_DisplayImage" src="/Services/UserControls/UploadHandlers/MediaServerHandler.ashx?id=465"/>
</div>
</div>
<h3 id="member51">Dr Julia Chisholm</h3>
<p><em>Consultant Paediatric Oncologist with an interest in Sarcoma and Young People</em></p>
<p>Dr Chisholm spent ten years as a consultant at Great Ormond Street  Hospital before moving to The Royal Marsden in 2010 to share  responsibility for the development of the new TYA service. Her interests  include the introduction of new therapies into soft tissue sarcoma  (especially rhabdomyosarcoma) and supportive care, particularly the  management of infection. Her focus is on developing an excellent  clinical service and improving the experience and outcomes of children  and young people undergoing cancer therapy.</p>
<p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:julia.chisholm@rmh.nhs.uk">julia.chisholm@rmh.nhs.uk</a></p>
</div>
<div class="staff-info pad">
<h4>Qualifications</h4>
<p>BMBCh</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
